13.3:
Consider
and hear me, O LORD my God: lighten mine eyes, lest I sleep the
sleep of death;

17.9:
From the wicked that oppress me,
from my deadly enemies,
who compass me about.

31.19:
Oh how great
is thy goodness, which thou hast laid up for them that fear thee;
which thou hast wrought for them that trust in thee before the sons of men!

45.5:
Thine arrows
are sharp in the heart of the king’s enemies;
whereby the people fall under thee.

45.12:
And the daughter of Tyre
shall be there with a gift;
even the rich among the people shall intreat thy favour.

47.2:
For the LORD most high
is terrible;
he is a great King over all the earth.

57.5:
Be thou exalted, O God, above the heavens;
let thy glory
be above all the earth.

62.2:
He only
is my rock and my salvation;
he is my defence; I shall not be greatly moved.

62.8:
Trust in him at all times;
ye people, pour out your heart before him: God
is a refuge for us. Selah.

65.5:
By terrible things in righteousness wilt thou answer us, O God of our salvation;
who art the confidence of all the ends of the earth, and of them that are afar off
upon the sea:

67.6:
Then shall the earth yield her increase;
and God,
even our own God, shall bless us.

73.20:
As a dream when
one awaketh;
so, O Lord, when thou awakest, thou shalt despise their image.

74.3:
Lift up thy feet unto the perpetual desolations;
even all
that the enemy hath done wickedly in the sanctuary.

78.60:
So that he forsook the tabernacle of Shiloh, the tent
which
 he placed among men;

89.50:
Remember, Lord, the reproach of thy servants;
how I do bear in my bosom
the reproach of all the mighty people;

91.5:
Thou shalt not be afraid for the terror by night;
nor for the arrow
that flieth by day;

91.9:
Because thou hast made the LORD,
which is my refuge,
even the most High, thy habitation;

103.21:
Bless ye the LORD, all
ye his hosts;
ye ministers of his, that do his pleasure.

105.10:
And confirmed the same unto Jacob for a law,
and to Israel
for an everlasting covenant:

106.4:
Remember me, O LORD, with the favour
that thou bearest unto
 thy people: O visit me with thy salvation;

107.10:
Such as sit in darkness and in the shadow of death,
being
 bound in affliction and iron;

114.6:
Ye mountains,
that ye skipped like rams;
and ye little hills, like lambs?

132.2:
How he sware unto the LORD,
and vowed unto the mighty
God of Jacob;

135.13:
Thy name, O LORD,
endureth for ever;
and thy memorial, O LORD, throughout all generations.

136.10:
To him that smote Egypt in their firstborn: for his mercy
endureth
 for ever:

136.11:
And brought out Israel from among them: for his mercy
endureth
 for ever:

136.13:
To him which divided the Red sea into parts: for his mercy
endureth
 for ever:

136.21:
And gave their land for an heritage: for his mercy
endureth
 for ever:

136.23:
Who remembered us in our low estate: for his mercy
endureth
 for ever:

141.5:
Let the righteous smite me;
it shall be a kindness: and let him reprove me;
it shall be an excellent oil,
which shall not break my head: for yet my prayer also
shall be in their calamities.

149.6:
Let the high
praises of God
be in their mouth, and a twoedged sword in their hand;
